Description:
The application uses analytics software that fetches the URL specified in the Referer header when a product page is loaded.
This behavior is vulnerable to Out-of-Band SSRF.

Objective:
-Trigger an HTTP request to Burp Collaborator
-Confirm SSRF via external interaction

Tools Used:
Burp Suite (Proxy, Repeater, Collaborator)

Exploitation Steps:
1️-Intercept Request
-Navigate to any product page
-Intercept the request using Burp Suite

2️-Send to Repeater
-Forward the request to Burp Repeater

3️-Inject Collaborator Payload
-Locate the Referer header
-Right-click → Insert Collaborator Payload
-This replaces the original URL with a unique Burp Collaborator domain

4️-Send Request
-Send the modified request

5️-Check for Interaction
-Go to Burp Collaborator tab
-Click Poll now
If no result appears:
-Wait a few seconds
-Poll again (execution is asynchronous)

Result:
-Received DNS and HTTP interactions from the target server
-Successfully confirmed Out-of-Band SSRF vulnerability
